- select reticle with name "HMD, Nikko Stirling"
- Tap the "Settings" button on the reticle screen and UNcheck the checkbox "This reticle is in the First Focal Plane (FFP)
- Enter Min. magnigification as 3
- Enter magnification the reticle was calibrated for. This is 9. Check this value in  scope manual
 - Enter max. magnification as 9

Igor has hit a home run with this one. (His other Strelok apps are just as awesome I have all 3).   The results are dead on.  I hit a 4"x6" @ 750 yd first shot. Igor also pays attention to the reviews and emails. If you want a new feature or reticle and he thinks it's a good idea wait a few days  and you will see it on an update. A+ in my book.
This app works great if you know all your settings...Usually gets me within .5 of a mil..

content: Absolutely the BEST ballistics calculator I have seen to date! Keep the updates coming! Very well thought out and efficiently laid out. Quick and easy to input/ use.

Works very well out of the box. Did my first shot on 450 and hit target. This program is as accurate as the data it receives. You give bad data and it won't be accurate. Feb really helpful and responds on emails.
A great and easy to use app! I use for airguns and have taken shots in long range and windy conditions that I never would have tried before.
I would have paid for the free version and the + version is even better. Worth every penny.

This is a good app but I'd like to able to set wind as part of the zeroing weather and have the app calculate the difference to the current wind speed/direction instead of assuming they're the same as it does now.

Have used Strelok for about a year now. Once you get good, accurate data for the computer, it rolls out the good stuff. If you don't have a reticule that tracks well with the turrets, you can still make good hits with the visual reticule feature.   Maybe not as exactingly accurate as Ballistic AE, but is less expensive, easily used, and very accurate once data is verified.  Also, it's available for android!  Hebrew soldier approved!  Izzy

I had the free version for a bit, blown away buy the paid. WOW!! Igor doesn't just sit by and let the program sit UN updated, since I got it he has updated it many time. Most of them have been new scopes, but this program works flawlessly! Now with GPS elevation and using the camera for angel adjustments, I can hardly wait for his next idea! Not sure where he gets the time to responded to all of his emails, but I've sent him three and all were responded too. If you're a shooter get this app!! Thanks Igor

Better than the free version. Strelok+ will correct your muzzle velocity based on where your shots are actually hitting. It maintains all the great features of the free version while adding in more scope adjustment between first or second focal plane, and adjustable zoom. If you take the time to input every detail, you will hit your target with a cold bore shot.  Developer is constantly adding updates and more features.

content: Great app for long range! I use it with several of my guns, but the most impressive is when using with my 22lr and UTG Mildot! Long range with a .22 can be tricky because of bullet drop. This app helped me reach out & was right on at 400 yards! Only downfall is my reticle is not listed, but u found a 9 mildot option that will get the job done! Great app and worth EVERY penny!!!
